        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 11 at 5:42PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 541 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a gust front/outflow
boundary producing strong winds ahead of a cluster of showers and
thunderstorms along a line extending from Clarksville City to near
Longview to near Hallsville to near Tatum to near Beckville.
Movement was northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Longview, Marshall, White Oak, Gladewater, Hallsville, Tatum, Ore
City, Clarksville City, Beckville, East Mountain, Diana, Harleton,
Easton, Union Grove, Warren City, Nesbitt, Darco, and Judson.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
